<TITLE> Portugal held to home draw by Albania's 10 men </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BRAGA, Portugal, Oct 16 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Portugal's faltering World Cup qualifying campaign continued when they were held to a dismal 0-0 draw by 10-man Albania on Wednesday. Carlos Queiroz's team, who have won only one of their four Group One qualifiers, were thwarted by Albania keeper Arian Beqaj who pulled off a series of good saves. The visitors went down to 10 men on the stroke of halftime when substitute Admir Teli was sent off following two bookable offences. Portugal piled on the pressure in the second period but Beqaj proved unbeatable. "We didn't expect to draw but I'd like to say that, even without producing a fantastic exhibition of football, I don't know what else we could do to win," coach Queiroz told reporters. "The players dominated the match and did everything to win. Make no mistake we will get the points we need to qualify." Portugal squandered two golden chances late on when striker Hugo Almeida headed against the post and Nani failed to hit the target after a clever back heel from Nuno Gomes. The 30,000 crowd delivered a chorus of whistles when the home team left the field. "It was a fantastic result especially because we just played with a player less all the second half, said Albania coach Arie Haan. "For us, it is a great result, we did a great job. A draw with 10 men in Portugal was very good
